# migrated from tests/cases/conjunction.it.chat (hermetic + isolated, perf-held)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test conjunction.it]
!timeout 0
# gen133, Italian probe: the SAME conjunctive-concept machinery through Italian
# surface ("ogni cane amichevole è un bravo"). One mechanism, two languages, one
# code path — the bilingual ratchet over rule intake, article-free assertion,
# abduction and robustness together.

> ogni cane amichevole è un bravo
< Learned rule: bravo(X) :- cane(X), amichevole(X).
> rex è un cane
< Learned: cane(rex).
> rex è un bravo?
< No.
> cosa renderebbe rex un bravo?
< If you told me that rex is a amichevole, then rex would be a bravo — that's the rule cane and amichevole -> bravo.
> rex è amichevole
< Learned: amichevole(rex). Now rex is a bravo after all.
> rex è un bravo?
< Yes.
> da cosa dipende?
< My conclusion that rex is a bravo rests on 2 load-bearing facts: cane(rex), amichevole(rex). Removing any one would overturn it.

